[[=]]
+ The Lost Paths Initiative
[[/=]]
----




@@ @@
[[=image https://lounge.hexick.com/uploads/0a423dea78e5984d/image.png style="width: 50px;"]]
[[=]]
[[size 200%]]Site-111[[/size]]
[[size 150%]]-- 2022 --[[/size]]
[[/=]]
------


Agent Fritz pulled the strange postcard out of the mailbox and yet again found a dreaded containment breach waiting to happen inside. Bizarre mail like this had been bombarding Site-111 and all the nearby facilities for weeks now, claiming to be from a self-proclaimed "para-tourism" agency with access to Ways leading into the long-sanctioned and forbidden Greater Earth. Fritz had placed himself in charge of deciphering their messages, finding both the presumably massive-scale breach of Veil security implied by the self-proclaimed agency's ability to go back and forth from the Outer Realms and the Foundation's oddly lax response to it all deeply concerning. No Foundation facility in the modern world still received snail-mail anyhow; since they were the only ones who delivered to the Site's mailbox, he had fast gained the joking reputation as the only one who checked it.

The letters and postcards taunted them, the wardens who held the keys that locked the planet away from itself and its magic, by offering to show them everything they denied themselves and the world. They had chosen the name Sheba -- the Queen of Sheba being the biblical figure who came to Jerusalem bearing gifts for King Solomon -- he suspected, because they must have fancied themselves the enlightened nobles overseeing a sickly, Veiled world, and out of their endless generosity had chosen to offer gifts tempting knowledge of the World-Left-Behind to the ignorant footsoldiers in the ranks of that great totality whose control they so loathed in the hopes that they would change their ways.

They had come like Pandora, offering a bounty that when opened would unleash the vexing plagues that would be the Jailors' undoing. Rather, this was how he suspected they thought of themselves.

@@ @@
----
@@ @@

[[div class="classification_memo"]]

The Veil-threatening entity sending communications to Foundation Sites starting with the incident on 27 May 2022 has tentatively been classified GoI-8181-P. For those curious, a log of incidents caused by this entity thusfar has been attached to the end of this transmission, accessible upon request to all personnel of clearance level 2 or above.

â€” Jean Karlyle Aktus, Director, USINBL Site-81

[[/div]]

@@ @@

[[div class="log-header"]]
**Date:** 27 May 2022

**Location:** Site-111

**Event:** GoI-8181-P sends a postcard allegedly addressed from the Acid-Wastes of Thirmyskirah, advertising a luxury beach vacation at the area in question and urging the reader to bathe in the acid pools on account that "the water's fine", among other allusions to several similar pool and jacuzzi-related expressions.
[[/div]]

[[div class="log-header"]]
**Date:** 29 May 2022

**Location:** Site-92

**Event:** GoI-8181-P sends a series of flyers alluding to an available hiking trip in the mountain peaks above Nidavellir. Advertisements claim that local mountain dwarf tribes constitute "porters" willing to carry the bags of potential travelers, and assure that the risk of being devoured by rogue lindwurms (//draco linnormr//) is "low". 
[[/div]]

[[div class="log-header"]]
**Date:** 29 May 2022

**Location:** Site-111

**Event:** GoI-8181-P sends a postcard alleged addressed from the Canyon of Zechnys in the Shattered Hills of Kalaphastia. Supposed attractions include skydiving, amateur geology, and riding the occult pterodactyloid psychopomps who glide across the skies above. Provided material reassures readers that the organisms in question will not in fact take them to any of 6,599 recorded afterlife dimensions associated with the manifestation of this type of postmortal organism, but rather for a safe and exciting ride across the mountains and canyons during which they will remain alive.
[[/div]]

[[div class="log-header"]]
**Date:** 2 June 2022

**Location:** Site-111

**Event:** GoI-8181-P advertises rock-climbing at the Moon-Spire of Tel'Aashqir. Flyers promise climbers who can make their way to the top of the spire while avoiding "any and all haunting attempts by vengeful lunar ghosts, ill-dreaming hiveminds, and trash-gods scavenging the dead grounds below" will receive a box of authentic lunar regolith as their prize.
[[/div]]

[[div class="log-header"]]
**Date:** 3 June 2022

**Location:** Site-34

**Event:** GoI-8181-P sends a flyer advertising a month-long cultural exchange trip to the insectoid citadel of Phosphornest, promising "a 100% genuine creepy-crawly cultural experience" wherein one will "learn to live authentically as if they too were a chitinous hexapod". Advertised activities include aphid-hunting, learning to pollinate and harvest nectar from flowers, and grueling manual labor in a hive.
[[/div]]

@@ @@
----
@@ @@

[[div class="email"]]
[[div class="tofrom"]]
**From:** Cyrus (Site-111 Administration, Site Director)
**To:** Fritz Williams (Dept. of Field Expeditions, Site-111 Station)
**Date:** 5/10/2022
**Subject:** re:The Lost Paths Initiative
[[/div]]
------
Dear Fritz Willie,

It is the honor and duty of Site-111 administration to inform you that, on request of relevant high Veil maintenance authorities and with oversight and request of the Extradimensional Relations Division, you have been reassigned to a special field mission. Please consult the attached document for additional information.

[[div class="modal"]]

Given the recent emergence of GoI-8181-P and the threat that its outreach capabilities could become global, the Foundation has seen it fit to determine whether GoI-8181-P indeed possesses metaspatial transport abilities or methods capable of breaching from baseline reality into congruospatial anomalogeographic subdimensions in violation of the relevant 1881 charter on sanctioning of passage between the Veiled world and non-authorized accessory paranormal frontiers. 

To this end, it has been deemed necessary for a field mission to attempt use of GoI-8181-P's services and determine if their purported methods of extradimensional transport are valid. Additionally, relevant authorities have authorized this mission, deemed the Lost Paths Initiative as an opportunity for the chosen agent(s) to explore and rediscover key-interest areas of the Outer Frontiers to acquire information in areas where that currently available to the Foundation may be outdated. 

The advising Extradimensional Relations Division has worked in collaboration with Field Operations chiefs to arrive at the attached agent recommended for the Lost Paths Initiative. We believe the chosen operative's extensive field proficiency in unpredictable, poorly-mapped and/or hostile environments combined with his dual academic experience in pre-Veil anomalous matters will prove very complementary to the stipulations of the initiative; the agent in question should be made aware, however, that the task required of him will constitute outreach into anomalous frontier dimensions long uncontacted by the Foundation or any other known baseline actor, carrying extensive potential risks from lack of experience, available information regarding, and Foundation presence in these areas. If he wishes to reject the mission, my office must be informed as such by Saturday at 12:00 PM.

[[/div]]

Sincerely,
Cyrus
Secure, Contain, Protect.

[[/div]]

@@ @@
----
@@ @@

[[div class="document"]]

**5/10/2022**

Apparently the Foundation has chosen me to take up whoever's sending those Sheba & Co. flyers on their offer. Command needs somebody to go where they say in their messages to see if they actually have a stable gate to the Outer World and then report accordingly so it can be disabled. Those guys have been harassing us with all sorts of weird, cryptic invitations for weeks; my bets are on some sort of meta-embodiment of our Veil haunting us, assuming they aren't a legit company. It isn't impossible they're just some thusfar-uncontacted extradimensional GoI with no idea who they're sending their mailers to, but then you'd probably expect they'd try to contact the public. Instead, whatever these guys are -- people? entities? UAEs? unknown Veiled actors? the correct term aside -- they //only// do their magic spam mail gimmick on our facilities, and so targetedly they just have to be playing with us somehow. Wouldn't be unexpected -- more and more small GoIs popping out of the woodworks and thinking they can mess with us as some sort of sick joke lately, especially since the Impasse for some reason.

Anyhow, assuming I'm not killed outright, I actually expect to stay out in the great beyond for quite a while. If what 8181-P's messages say is true, with the places they advertise, I'd be the first human from the Prime Earth to go so far out into the Outer World since we closed them off -- at least so far as the Foundation knows, anyway. My duties are to record whatever I see out there and hope I get back alive to return it: telecomms aren't believed to work since we cut the Hyperways, so I've brought a big stack of leather notebooks instead. Once they leave me at my destination, I'll hit all the nearby areas to take notes and make observations; just base-level review for curiosity, since we haven't checked on what's going on out there presumably for over a century.

I'll check in later if I need to get more thoughts down. No time to process now, though -- work to be done. I'm stepping into the untamed wilds the Foundation locked out and hasn't gone back in for well over a century; there must have been a reason why they did, and I'm taking every necessary precaution to be ready for whatever it is.

[[/div]]

@@ @@
