@@ @@

[[include :scp-wiki:component:id-card |css=--
|photo=https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/46/ASCAN_2021_Class_Wilderness_Survival_Training_-_Jack_Hathaway.jpg/640px-ASCAN_2021_Class_Wilderness_Survival_Training_-_Jack_Hathaway.jpg
|level=3
|name=Fritz Williams
|dept=Field Expeditions
|position=Agent
|id-number= 6690-710350
|expiry= 8/19/2029
]]

[[div class="jotting"]]

Agent Fritz has served with the Foundation in various field ops capacities for over 20 years. He is permanently affiliated with no Task Force and his record indicates he is conventionally best as a solo non-combat asset, with prior deployments mostly involving locating or surveilling objects that will not require immediate combat engagement in anomalous environments, as well as surveying anomalous locations that are poorly-mapped and unpredictable. To this end he has repeatedly gained accreditation in previous deployments as adaptable and a highly-skilled survivalist; file indicates basic physical combat training (despite a mainly non-combat deployment record), proficiency in improvised anti-thaumatological techniques, and at least basic knowledge of 20 or more anomalous and non-anomalous languages.

We recommend him on the basis that the environs covered by the Lost Paths Initiative are not extensively recorded or understood and will likely be dangerous or otherwise unpredictable, and humbly request the directorship of Site-111 and associated central authorities at the Department of Field Expeditions to grant us Agent Fritz as the subject of the Initiative and extradite him to Dimensional Outpost-1981 as soon as is convenient.

Fritz and the other candidates before him have already been inoculated with [https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/pickman-blank-proposal Antimeme-001] counteractant and amnesticized; thus, he is already proofed against the possibility of discovering that "Sheba & Co. Paranormalcy", the agency invented to justify this breach in the Foundation's traditional policy of isolation against the Outer Realms for the sake of necessary exploration and inquiry, is indeed a Foundation front company.

Concludingly, we ascertain that Agent Fritz will provide the crucial human element necessary to provide the Extradimensional Relations Division with a body of knowledge sufficient enough that, augmented with our current drone surveillance, Greater Earth can soon be comprehensively mapped and more fully understood by all for the good of the Foundation.

[[=]]
**//Secure, Contain, Protect.//**
[[/=]]

[[/div]]



